BlackNova Traders - Readme

A web-based massively multi-player strategy game of space trading and combat.

Version 0.37
http://www.blacknova.net

Copyright (C) 2000 Ron Harwood <harwoodr@blacknova.net>

This program is free software; you can redistribute it and/or modify it under 
the terms of the GNU Public License (see LICENSE or 
http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html)

This program is distributed in the hope that it will be useful,
but WITHOUT ANY WARRANTY; without even the implied warranty of
MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.  See the GNU Public
License for more details.

Requirements: 
    PHP4
    MySQL (tested with 3.23.x)
    ADODB
    a web-browser (doh!)

Download:
    You can get the newest version at http://blacknova.net

Credits:
    This work is based on the old BBS games that went by many names
    (Tradewars, Galactic Warzone, Yankee Trader, Ultimate Universe, and
    many other names like this) but shares no code with them.  It is
    written 100% in PHP/HTML.  
    Please refer to the DEVCREDIT file to see
    the current list of developers.

Installation:
    Please see the INSTALL file.

Upgrades:
    There have been numerous table changes, so upgrading is not supported.

ChangeLog:
    Please see the CHANGES file.    

Documentation:
    None to speak of yet.

Updates:
    Join the blacknova announcement mailing list to be informed of updates, patches 
    and new releases. Send an email to bnt-announce-request@thegeek.org with the single
    word subscribe in the body of the email.

Enjoy,

Ron Harwood <harwoodr@blacknova.net>

PS:  I would appreciate both an e-mail (if you are running BlackNova
Traders on your site) and a link back to the main blacknova site
http://blacknova.net - or better still join the blacknova banner exchange at
http://mybannerswap.com/mbs/at-accountedit.pl?account=new&webnetwork=blacknova

